The paper analyzes the uplink performance of a wireless network with base stations distributed according to a Poisson Point Process (PPP) and uses linear minimum-mean-square-error (MMSE) spatial processing for multiple access. This involves channel estimation and spectral efficiency, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of massive Multiple-Input-Multiple-Output (MIMO) systems, which falls under the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with cellular networks, which is a topic covered in the Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
